<title>Weather beaten</title>
<description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.flickr.com/photos/thomasguest/2740477283/&quot; title=&quot;Shellfish&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3073/2740477283_b290beb539_m.jpg&quot; width=&quot;177&quot; height=&quot;240&quot; alt=&quot;shellfish&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&amp;#8217;re back from holiday a few days earlier than planned. Even if you&amp;#8217;re camping in a field surrounded by sand-dunes and just a few hundred metres from the &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.cornwallbeachguide.co.uk/penwith/gwithian/gwithian.htm&quot;&gt;best beach in the world&lt;/a&gt;, the rain gets to you after a while.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Good:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;body-boarding, rock-pooling, fighting the waves&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;watching Isobel and Alex ride their bicycles around the campsite&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;reading&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;a &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.thealbarestaurant.com/&quot;&gt;memorable meal&lt;/a&gt; in St Ives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;the &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.tate.org.uk/stives/hepworth/&quot;&gt;Barbara Hepworth sculpture garden&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;clear roads, for once&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.tate.org.uk/stives/hepworth/&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://www.tate.org.uk/stives/hepworth/images/garden_in_spring.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;Sculpture garden&quot;/&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Not so good:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;gusting wind&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;ceaseless rain&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;damp shoes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;pulled muscle&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;car trouble&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.flickr.com/photos/thomasguest/2741314568/&quot; title=&quot;Mousehole harbour, in the rain&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3097/2741314568_c62067665a.jpg&quot; width=&quot;500&quot; height=&quot;165&quot; alt=&quot;mousehole&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
